=====<br>
how does a skald have better survivability?<br>
<br>
Ablative + evade + shield + dex makes for a passable defense against most MTs, you said that your skald outdamages a warrior earlier, well thats really an issue of over time. over time a warrior will last longer then a skald and will cause more end damage with a 1h/shield then a skald will.  Skalds eventually will run out of power and then you are just left with your weapon attacks, which are affected by your lowered weapon skill (you didn't say what the weaponskills were on your toons).  however, that being said.  a Main Tank with a shield equiped vs a minst has to contend with the lower per hit damage which means that their damage per hit is more significantly affected by ablative procs.   Compare that to a skald who will, in a moderately buffed state, take close to full damage over time from a main tank , simply because their defense is so poor they rarely evade/block/parry, and a main tanks is so high that they rarely out right miss.  as a result, the skald is less survivable in that instance then a minst is simply because they have no chant that helps their defense, only a moderately effective offensive chant which is subject to being completely nullified by block, parry, evade.  it doesn't equal out, a minst is more survivable then a skald is.<br>
<br>
compare next to keep sieges, a minst's ablative will allow them to contest most guards, absorbing substantial portions of the incoming damage, their ability to mezz while kiting also allows them greater effective survivability against medium to low guards, with about the same survivability vs lvl 8+ guards and relic guards.<br>
<br>
 a defensive stun and followup mezz ability gives them a far better escape mechanism then say a skald shout mezz + snare, which is only moderately useful at best.<br>
<br>
Now compare group viability between the two<br>
<br>
skald brings resist chants which overwrite shammy/healer resists<br>
skald brings a DA with  limited damage add ( a paltry 7 dps, if you spec that high, which many are chooosing not too)<br>
a skald brings speed, the rest song is more or less useless and you can't twist them.<br>
<br>
now look at minst <br>
<br>
Ingoring pets for the moment<br>
they have a power regen song<br>
ablative chant<br>
secondary CC<br>
speed<br>
<br>
<br>
Now compare the effectiveness of a skald and a minst using crocodile tears ring, which must now be accounted for in terms of balance because of the major advantage it gives albs.<br>
<br>
skald, minst both have same speed.  Draw.<br>
<br>
Skald has DA, wide area effect, only benefits classes who melee.<br>
<br>
minst has ablative, wide area effect, stacks with other effects similiar to how RM BT works, benefits ALL classes, regardless of spec. May or may not continue to benefit guards also, including keep lords.  Why this is major?  well you don't hit a lvl 10 keep lord all that hard, or a relic guard all that hard to start with, having 60-70 of that damage you did then absorbed by a realm effective ablative starts to really compound problems with keep sieges/relic raids.<br>
<br>
Rest song for skalds is bleh, hardly worth using, might be good for resting after an epic mob raid, if that.<br>
<br>
power regen song, effects everyone with a power pool, very nice for pallys, clerics, casters, doesn't do too shabby when linked in with necro power transfer either.  huge bonus for both pve and rvr.<br>
<br>
Skald resist chants, this will actually be HARMFUL to use with that ring.  it would overwrite a ton of other peoples shammy/healer buffs for a single/short duration series of pulses that skip.<br>
<br>
that's just one example of the disparity between artifacts for skalds/minst.<br>
<br>
we can debate other aspects of it all day. but the bottom line is the following<br>
<br>
skalds CAN obtain decent damage with great gear + buffs<br>
skalds are only moderately needed in rvr anymore (crocodile tears ring makes it so you need 1 skald for whole army now, further decreasing the reasons to group skalds)<br>
skalds&lt; minst in terms of survivability, you can argue this all you want, but there are no numbers to support that its any other case then this.  It's simply fact.<br>
Skalds &lt; minst in terms of group benefits<br>
Skald utility &lt; minst in both keep sieges and pve (climb walls, mezz etc etc)<br>
<br>
Skald shout being reduced to 15 second recast certainly was a nice change, but the fact that minst, in the common spec also got a lvl 50 dd at the same time could hardly be considered beneficial to the balance of the two classes. it remains a cold hard fact that the &quot;support based&quot; minst class can kick the crap out of the melee based combat class  (skald) if they are played by anyone with even a reasonable amount of talent.  add in pets to the matter, which IMHO you will see a LOT more of when more crocodile tears rings get out, and suddenly its not even close to balanced anymore. (CT ring will allow one-two minst to run speed for everyone, allowing the rest to get a nice pet)<br>
<br>
there are quite a few minor issues that if fixed would for the most part fix a lot of the problems skalds face, however when that report with those suggested fixes was submitted (1.61) it was essentially ignored. then months later we see the changes in the Warlord ML path, available to other classes, again returning us to teh status we've been in for going on 17 months, which is a class decreasing in usefullness.<br>
<br>
I think your assessment that people are whining about skalds is way off, i think you've gotten a inflated view of their effectiveness, that has thus skewed your analysis. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://bellsouthpwp.net/d/o/donatea/x/sig-auren.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ravensonghausakluif>Ravensong Hausakluif</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#ff0000>(12/17/03 7:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=767.topic&index=33>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Great Job!</span><hr size=1> Wow Sligg, thank you for the personal attacks.  You have, at the very least, shown everyone here how immature you are.  Please take your narrow-minded vitriol back to the VN boards.  <br>
