<br>
Wow. Well I have to say your understanding of RvR and priorities is a bit out of whack. First off, a good player in RvR will understand that there are three classifications of targets: Priority or Important targets (Any caster, any healer), rogues and tanks. Priority targets are not killed first because they are the easiest to kill, although that is a factor. They are killed first because left unchecked they can singlehandedly destroy a group. Minstrels are in a different boat because of SoS. If they are mezzed and not purging, they are lower priority than any healer or caster. If they are unmezzed they are very high priority. Skalds are very low priority because they are a hybrid tank and not as easy to take down as any caster and tougher to take down than a healer (only because if you are on a skald rather than a healer, you have a healer free to heal the skald, while if on a healer, you have one less person distributing heals. <br>
