&quot;Sadly, what that normally means is that you ran around an held off fighting the majority of the fights you COULD engage (because the otherside was a bunch of clueless zerging noobs right?) until you found fights you could win, usually fights you either outnumber or you come up on people from the side, thus gaining initial contact advantage which immediately decreases the &quot;skill required&quot; to win simply because your enemy is disadvantaged from the get go.&quot;<br>
