Um. Well, I dunno what a lot of the 8v8 people do on your server, but it is standard practice for us to engage larger numbers. We don't run from anything unless they significantly outnumber us. Not sure how that is different from any other rvr engagement. It is pretty common for us to kill 3 or 4 groups. We have killed up to 50 or so in the open field, but that was a special battle with special circumstances. In any case, we don't bring 8 because we want to fight only other 8v8 groups (although those can be a lot of fun). We bring 8 because anything more isn't enough of a challenge. I know the concept of &quot;challenge&quot; is foreign to many people in DAoC, but I actually like to fight when the odds are stacked against me.<br>
<br>
&quot;The sad fact of the matter is that tho the skald performes moderately well in single group combat in combat situations where they are advantaged from the start, when you go head to head with groups where the fight is even or they start with the advantage you provide no significant bonus to your group. When you go against multiple enemy groups, the rest of your REALM'S force, gains an insignifcant advantage from you being there.&quot;<br>
